new file mode 100644
index 0000000..fd5e946
--- /dev/null
+++ b/SOLUTION.md
@@ -0,0 +1,14 @@
+# Solution
+
+Two bugs in `lrucache/cache.py`:
+
+1. **`get` did not refresh recency.** A successful `get` returned the value
+   without calling `move_to_end`, so reads never counted as "use" and a
+   recently-read key could still be evicted as the least recently used. Fixed
+   by moving the key to the end of the `OrderedDict` on a non-expired hit.
+
+2. **`put` evicted on updates of existing keys.** The eviction check
+   `len(self._data) >= self.capacity` ran unconditionally, so overwriting a
+   key in an already-full cache wrongly evicted the LRU entry even though the
+   size wasn't going to grow. Fixed by only evicting when the key being put is
+   not already present.
